Copyright (C) 2025 Peter Joseph — integralcollective.io

This software is developed through voluntary contribution for the purpose 
of building a post-monetary, cooperative economic system. It exists to 
serve participants in cooperative nodes — not to generate institutional 
revenue of any kind.

PERMISSIONS

You are free to:

- Use this software to operate a non-extractive cooperative node
- Study, modify, and adapt this software for that purpose
- Share this software and your modifications with others under 
  these same terms

CONDITIONS

Any modifications you make must be released under this same license. 
If you run this software as a network service, you must make the 
complete source code of your running version available under these 
same terms.

PROHIBITIONS

You may not:

- Sell this software or any derivative of it
- Use this software as the technical basis of any product or service 
  for which money, fees, donations, subscriptions, grants, or any 
  other form of institutional revenue is charged or received
- Package, bundle, or deploy this software in support of any 
  institution — whether for-profit, nonprofit, cooperative, or 
  otherwise — that derives income from its use
- Use this software to facilitate any platform, marketplace, or 
  service that intermediates between participants for commercial gain

This prohibition applies regardless of the legal structure of the 
entity involved. The nonprofit legal form does not exempt an 
organization from this restriction. The test is not legal structure 
— it is whether the software is being used to extract money from 
its operation.

PERMITTED USE

This software may be used freely by:

- Participants operating Integral nodes for their own communities
- Contributors developing and improving the software itself
- Researchers and students studying the system for non-commercial 
  educational purposes

NO WARRANTY

This software is provided as-is, without warranty of any kind. 
The authors are not liable for any damages arising from its use.

INTENT

This license exists because the software it governs was built to 
transcend institutional economic logic — not to be absorbed by it. 
Anyone who uses this software to extract money from others, in any 
form, has violated the spirit and the letter of the terms under 
which it was created.
